    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is HTML Accessibility?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "HTML accessibility ensures that websites are usable by everyone, including people with disabilities. It improves usability for screen readers, keyboard navigation, and assistive technologies."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Accessibility Matters"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Inclusivity** – Everyone can access your content",
        "**Legal Compliance** – Required in many countries",
        "**Better UX** – Improves usability for all users",
        "**SEO Benefits** – Search engines favor accessible sites"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Use Semantic HTML"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Semantic elements like <header>, <nav>, <main>, and <footer> help screen readers understand page structure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Alt Text for Images"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"image.jpg\" alt=\"Description of image\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Accessible Forms"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<label for=\"name\">Name:</label>\n<input id=\"name\" type=\"text\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "ARIA Attributes"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications) attributes provide additional information for assistive technologies."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<button aria-label=\"Close\">X</button>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Keyboard Accessibility"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Ensure all interactive elements can be accessed using a keyboard (Tab, Enter, Space)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Color Contrast"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Use sufficient contrast between text and background to improve readability."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Accessible Links"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<a href=\"/about\">Read more about our services</a>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use semantic HTML elements**",
        "**Provide alt text for images**",
        "**Use labels for form inputs**",
        "**Ensure keyboard navigation**",
        "**Maintain good color contrast**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Missing alt attributes**",
        "**Using div instead of semantic tags**",
        "**Poor color contrast**",
        "**Not supporting keyboard navigation**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "HTML accessibility ensures that web content is usable for everyone. Following accessibility practices improves inclusivity, SEO, and overall user experience."
    }
